originalText.text: Looking at old photos. Blast from the past. Stayed here in 1979, our last night in US after a 6 week trek across America. I remember it as a beautiful building and lobby, but the room was a bit tat. Lol. Happy days.

originalText.text: omg I was staying here sometime in 1985 I was about 20/21 it was me and my 2 lil sons ..it was scary for me at 1st ..this place is huge and it was so nice and quiet when we stayed here..my room was 542 a nice small room with a nice bathroom and a spacious closet ..I can't even write enough to tell how this turned out to be one of the best Elegant places I've ever lived ..I will Never forget Prince George Hotel..I had so much fun there.. from having maid service to eating at the diner in the Latham hotel 1st FL..and the restaurant on the corner of 28th and Madison ave..sitting in Madison Square park when Caucassion people wasn't afraid of a Black personü§ó ..my kids were ages 3 and 7 well behaved and decent we had lunch in the park it was so beautiful and quiet the whole 1st year but that next year ..some wild unruly people came to stay at Prince George..and that's when it became terrible and the peace was gone ..but I stayed out if trouble I had just a few friends but I mostly stayed to myself .. my kids went to a nice school and not the ghetto one they sent most of the kids to ..( the  Bleeker st area school.. ü§î anyway I love this place and I wish I could own it someday .. Thank you Prince George Hotel.. you are and were Amazing to me and my lil ones..‚ù§‚ù§‚ù§‚ù§.. I'm in tears üò¢ but Thank you all so much for those who worked there in those years.. I was there from about 85-88.. I was always treated with respect and that's how I carried myself ..with Respect.. originalText.text: This Building is Beautifully Preserved and Restored.. The Lobby and Front Desk are Breathtaking.... Despite a few very Strict and Silly safety rules I bet this would be a great place to call home....

originalText.text: Visited this beautiful building as a volunteer to help serving food at the opening of an art show by residents. Everything was well organized by the staff and the art work impressive.
